  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Update to Ganache v7 should be faster than v6, but many users don't experience this in many (most?) cases as Truffle's web3 must poll for changes (example: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-upgrades/pull/523).\r\n\r\nIf truffle updates to using WebSockets this polling behavior won't occur. In the meantime, I think we should switch our default mode to \"eager\" (which is also Ganache v7's default).\r\n\r\nThere _is_ a way to make Ganache behave as if it was in eager mode for messages sent over HTTP connections only, but doing it is very hacky and gross, as it makes the RPC logic change based on the connection kind. So I'd rather not do this (I actually [did do it already](https://github.com/trufflesuite/ganache/compare/3acc35e2e121e8ef2bcebbb3aa5eeec360fc58cf...8b15e3c1aebc4c99a217438fad3d1c208c662f5e), and it really is horrible).",
